00:48:59,658 --> 00:49:01,319
Basically, this meant that the songs

466
00:49:01,379 --> 00:49:03,360
would transition to instrumental arrangements

467
00:49:03,420 --> 00:49:05,801
in between sections if the player hung around

468
00:49:05,841 --> 00:49:07,362
in a particular area for too long.

469
00:49:08,063 --> 00:49:12,467
For example, ensuring that verses and choruses never repeated unnaturally.

470
00:49:14,029 --> 00:49:17,612
We also made heavy use of WISER's entry and exit cues to ensure the

471
00:49:17,652 --> 00:49:19,514
transitions themselves felt natural.

